# Frontend Experience

- RULE: Design mobile-first and Safari-first.
- RULE: Keep product UI Spanish-first with English as the secondary locale.
- RULE: Keep repository-facing content in English.
- RULE: Favor stable browser APIs and lightweight frontend decisions that work well on WebKit.
- RULE: Support both light and dark presentation and default to the system color-scheme preference.
- RULE: Target WCAG 2.2 AA in product decisions and avoid public conformance claims until the relevant UI slice is actually audited.
- RULE: Use `Home`, `Planner`, and `Calendario` as the primary public navigation destinations.
- RULE: Keep community/help and AI-connection surfaces secondary to the primary navigation.
- RULE: Start the product flow with onboarding inside the planner flow, not behind an account wall.
- RULE: Collect entry term in onboarding with controlled season/year selectors instead of free-text input.
- RULE: Derive onboarding year-selector options from the published catalog applicability window instead of exposing arbitrary years.
- RULE: Hide plan selection until the entry-term selectors are complete enough to filter candidate plans.
- RULE: Keep `/` as the public home, `/planner` as the dedicated planner shell, `/planner/onboarding` as the embedded planner-onboarding route, and `/calendar` as the public calendar surface.
- RULE: Keep `/planner` safe even when onboarding is incomplete; browser-side redirects may be used, but the route must still expose a stable fallback path to `/planner/onboarding`.
- RULE: Treat stale browser-local profile state as incomplete when the current published catalog no longer yields an applicable active plan for the stored entry term.
- RULE: Keep the initial planner document lean and fetch heavy schedule detail from precomputed JSON on demand instead of embedding the full catalog detail into the first HTML response.
- RULE: Keep planner onboarding as a guided stepper with explicit back/next progression and a lightweight introductory step.
- RULE: Collect entry term, searchable deduplicated program choice, and preferred swipe-direction mode during planner onboarding.
- RULE: Deduplicate visible plan rows into alphabetized searchable program choices whenever the selected entry term exposes multiple rows for the same program title.
- RULE: Treat launch planner widget preferences as browser-local UI state, initialize the default launch widget set during planner setup, and keep `Today` visually dominant when present.
- RULE: Recover silently from browser-owned state failures whenever possible and never expose storage-reset internals in routine UI copy.
- RULE: If a visible runtime error state is unavoidable, keep it generic and keep the surrounding route alive.
- RULE: Never wipe browser-local planner state automatically just because a route-level error boundary rendered.
- RULE: Keep an explicit `Under Construction` notice visible while the product is still in scaffold-heavy mode.
- RULE: Treat SEO, crawlability, and structured metadata as product requirements.
- RULE: Drive visible UI strings, selector labels, and locale-dependent option labels from locale configuration instead of hardcoded component strings.
- RULE: Keep planner logic, browser persistence, and presentation styling loosely coupled so the visual system can be replaced without rewriting behavior.
- RULE: Keep swipe navigation scoped to the top navigation surface only.
- RULE: Persist the chosen or learned swipe-direction preference browser-locally without changing the semantic destination set.
- RULE: Keep any setup/loading transition browser-local, bounded, and purely cosmetic.
- RULE: Do not instruct users to install the site through browser-native menu entries from within the website UI.
- RULE: Keep a small persistent legal footer with links to Terms and Privacy.
- RULE: Favor layered gradients, monochrome noise, and floating accent objects over large flat surfaces.
- RULE: Treat Apple atmosphere, Proton Authenticator web, and Perplexity Comet as inspiration only; never copy their assets, code, or distinctive strings.
- RULE: State clearly that no account is required.
- RULE: Treat the final Connect to ChatGPT route and setup flow as a follow-up slice after planner state exists.
